RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHEROKEE CASTLE chased inside, eased out toward the head of the lane and dug in under determined handling to get up the final strides. CAT WITH A NOTION set a pressured pace leaving the chute, raced near the rail on the turn and dug in under steady stretch encouragement, but was caught in the final strides. BLUE MOUNTAIN gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. AWESOME MOON gave chase, rounded the turn in the four path then flattened in the lane. WARRIORINTHEHOUSE dropped well back and saved ground.

SHERIFF'S KID broke awkwardly then saved ground. KALENJIN took over nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was met and gave chase approaching the three eighths pole but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and weakened.

WICKED SAUCY chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail and weakened in the lane. KILLDRESS KAY hesitated at the break and never factored.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARITABLY GIFTED chased and raced close in the three path on the turn, dueled to the front mid-stretch and drew clear under steady handling. LION OF THE SEA chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn, came between horses mid-stretch and held on for second. POLITICAL DECISION chased the pace, rounded the turn about the five path, left the turn outside and dug in to take third under the wire. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 7F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 38700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER SINCE OCTOBER 15, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ISHIHARA settled in the three path the first turn and stalked into the backstretch, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the far turn, dueled for the lead past the eighth pole and dug in to inch clear under the wire. FANCY CONCHO rated close inside, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail, eased out and took aim three wide at the eighth pole and finished evenly at the outside flank of the winner. PENGUIN POWER stumbled leaving the gate but recovered quickly and took over inside, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn, but was met past the eighth pole, flattened stride the final sixteenth and just lasted for third. COMMAND THE CAT settled off the rail on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path, dug in leaving the turn and just missed third. ALLEN CAN DO IT stalked off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then flattened in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Original Gold S. CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 90. Stakes Purse 75000. FOR REGISTERED ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. $50 nominations close Wednesday, April 05, 2023. $50 to enter with a purse of $75,000 Added. Entries close Wednesday, April 12, 2023 by the usual time of closing. T he added monies and all fees to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight: Three Years Old 117 lbs.; Older 126 lbs. Field will be limited to ten starters with up to four alternates. Preference to thos e horses having accumulated the highest 2022-2023 earnings at the time of closing of entries. Trophy to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCYLOU WHO tapered in and stalked the pace, challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole and took the nod two deep midway on the far turn, drew clear into the lane and was kept sharp to the wire. XANTHE settled back in the three path on the first turn, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and improved four wide on the far turn, was brushed lightly by Alpine Moon leaving the turn but closed for second inside the sixteenth pole. MOONLIT SHADOW took the lead while tapering to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, was met at the rail midway on the far turn then flattened stride the final furlong. ALPINE MOON settled in the three path on the opening turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn three wide, angled out and made light contact with Xanthe leaving the turn and flattened stride in the lane. THE SKY IS FALLING saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and flattened in the lane. CHANGE THE WORLD rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and flattened in the lane. AZZURRA rounded the first turn off the rail and showed little response through the backstretch. YOLO CHARLOTTE stalked from the three and four paths, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole then weakened off the rail on the far turn. SENECA ROCKS rated close inside on the opening turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. OCEAN LILLY saved ground. The Stewards reviewed and dismissed a claim of foul for alleged interference leaving the far turn, lodged by the rider of Alpine Moon, against the rider of Xanthe.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,chased 3/8,faded rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Moonlit Shadow
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 7/16,met rail mid turn,flattened

DUSTWHIRL WONDER showed little response. HURRICANE DIRECTOR stalked in the four path the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn. SCARLET TANAGER came away a bit rank and never factored.
